<div class='allCommunityAnswers'>
<div class='communityAnswer'>
<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/61788349-charles-egan"><img alt="" src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/users/1479773129i/61788349._UX100_CR0,25,100,100_.jpg" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/61788349-charles-egan">Charles Egan</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">Just a few ideas - <br/>1. Who do you think comes across as the strongest character?<br/>2. When Luke senses the vast power behind the mountain, is he having an<a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">Just a few ideas - <br />1. Who do you think comes across as the strongest character?<br />2. When Luke senses the vast power behind the mountain, is he having an epileptic seizure, or a vision of God?<br />3. What do you think of the use of newspaper extracts?<br />4. Do you think there is too much dialogue, or too little?<br />5. Google and read the last 4 lines of Goethe's 'Faust'. Then read the last 2 pages of the book again. Who represents the 'Eternal Feminine'?<br />6. To what extent do you feel The Killing Snows is a story of alienation?<br />7. What did you know of the Irish Famine before you read The Killing Snows?<br />8. Did you know there are now 2 sequels?<a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
</div>
</div>
