<span id="freeTextContainer2586448415381658258">DNF<br/><br/>I chose this book specifically because of the setting. I wanted to know more about the time and place and people of the Irish Famine. <br/><br/>So I give the book two stars because it was looking to address the importance of remembering that time. <br/><br/>The remarkable thing about it was that it managed to describe such a time of utter horror and tragedy in such a drab way. The characters were two dimensional and the writing pedestrian. I did learn about the period and would have probably learned more if I’d </span>
  <span id="freeText2586448415381658258" style="display:none">DNF<br /><br />I chose this book specifically because of the setting. I wanted to know more about the time and place and people of the Irish Famine. <br /><br />So I give the book two stars because it was looking to address the importance of remembering that time. <br /><br />The remarkable thing about it was that it managed to describe such a time of utter horror and tragedy in such a drab way. The characters were two dimensional and the writing pedestrian. I did learn about the period and would have probably learned more if I’d struggled through to the end but at 60% of the way through I packed it in. It was, bizarrely, boring. </span>
