<div id="review_1508997235" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1508997235" />
    <a title="Immergrün" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/33505147-immergr-n"><img alt="Immergrün" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1515317101p2/33505147.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1508997235?book_show_action=true">Jan 13, 2016</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Immergrün" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Immergrün" href="/user/show/33505147-immergr-n">Immergrün</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1508997235" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer1445262355663311175">This novel stands comfortably alongside other major works on the Great Famine like Liam O&apos;Flaherty&apos;s Famine or Joseph O&apos;Connor&apos;s The Star of the Sea. What sets Egan&apos;s work apart from the vast amount of historical romances is not just his deep understanding of the traumatic nature of the events, but also his differentiated portrayal of the time. </span>
  <span id="freeText1445262355663311175" style="display:none">This novel stands comfortably alongside other major works on the Great Famine like Liam O'Flaherty's Famine or Joseph O'Connor's The Star of the Sea. What sets Egan's work apart from the vast amount of historical romances is not just his deep understanding of the traumatic nature of the events, but also his differentiated portrayal of the time. </span>
  <a data-text-id="1445262355663311175" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
