<div id="review_4041149297" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/4041149297" />
    <a title="Betsy" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/95964377-betsy"><img alt="Betsy" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1643214893p2/95964377.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/4041149297?book_show_action=true">Oct 07, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Betsy" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Betsy" href="/user/show/95964377-betsy">Betsy</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Kindle Edition " href="/book/show/45785754-the-killing-snows">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer4041149297" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer15494328122808847320">The more I read of this period in Irish history, the more I feel the need to clarify the misunderstanding that this was not a famine........it was a great starvation. This horror could have been avoided. It is a story of the calculated strategy of one nation&apos;s attempt to eliminate another. One group of people saw another as inferior and made the decision that this population should be wiped out in the most inhumane and treacherous manner. Charles Egan&apos;s work of historical fiction, which I suspec</span>
  <span id="freeText15494328122808847320" style="display:none">The more I read of this period in Irish history, the more I feel the need to clarify the misunderstanding that this was not a famine........it was a great starvation. This horror could have been avoided. It is a story of the calculated strategy of one nation's attempt to eliminate another. One group of people saw another as inferior and made the decision that this population should be wiped out in the most inhumane and treacherous manner. Charles Egan's work of historical fiction, which I suspect to be accurate, provided me additional confirmation that this starvation actually took place, and insight into what has made the Irish and their descendants who they are today. It helps me understand the generations who came before me, including my own parents. It is a story that needs to be told and retold so like other stories where one people cruelly dominate another, it will not happen again, even though it seems we never learn. This is also a story of how the Irish truly rescued themselves.</span>
  <a data-text-id="15494328122808847320" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

