        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3222756719" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer8311847330422531757"><strong>Unbelievable horror </strong><br/><br/>I use these above words to describe the story line of this book ! Not because this is a work of fiction but because the “ unbelievable horror “ has been described in words that brings back the past of the Irish Nation and it’s Peoples suffering ! The only thing that can’t be brought forward is the smell !<br/><br/>I believe this book should be made into a movie with all of its hideous details not just of the actually happenings but also the feelings of guilt by not being able to help y</span>
  <span id="freeText8311847330422531757" style="display:none"><strong>Unbelievable horror </strong><br /><br />I use these above words to describe the story line of this book ! Not because this is a work of fiction but because the “ unbelievable horror “ has been described in words that brings back the past of the Irish Nation and it’s Peoples suffering ! The only thing that can’t be brought forward is the smell !<br /><br />I believe this book should be made into a movie with all of its hideous details not just of the actually happenings but also the feelings of guilt by not being able to help your neighbors and own Family !<br /><br />We need this book , story and possible movie to teach the generations far removed from this “ unbelievable horror “ that this indeed happen and damaged a Nation . The truth of the matter and Shame was that there was always enough food grown on the Island for everyone to eat but because of greed and prejudice! A whole Nation either died , emigrated or suffered ! Please read and honor those who endured! </span>
